Hi,
first of all, congratulations and many thanks for what you are offering us.

I am using `<st-sort>` in order to sort the columns of my table, but I would like to let the user know he can sort the columns.

Indeed, until he clicks on the `<th>Column Title</th>` There is nothing indicating the user he can sort the data in the table's columns.

So what I'm trying to achieve is to have by default both icons used in the following  css :
```css
.st-sort-ascent:before{
    content: '\25B2';
}

.st-sort-descent:before{
    content: '\25BC';
}
```

but in a gray (disabled) color in order to let the user know there is no sorting active.

This would look like this when no sort is active :  ![unactive](http://arts-crafts-publishing.com/images/components/arrow-sort.png), but preferably in a gray color to point there is no active sort at the moment.

And after a sort is applied, we could either keep the current icons or use somethink like this : ![active](http://www4.infoprintsolutionscompany.com/help/topic/com.infoprint.rpde.linux.base/graphics/sort_up_2012a.png).

How could I implement something like this ?


Regards,
Seifer

Namespaces are definitely a needed feature, as is an easier way to add attributes to tags. I propose this be done in the following way:

```python
dict = {
    "Envelope": {
        "_ns":    "soapenv",
        "_attrs": {
            "soapenv": { "_ns": "xmlns", "value": "http://schemas.xmlsoap.org/soap/envelope/" },
            "urn": { "_ns": "xmlns", "value": "urn:partner.soap.sforce.com" },
            "otherExample": "test value"
        },
        "Header": {
            "_ns":    "soapenv",
            "SessionHeader": {
                "_ns": "urn",
                "sessionId": "3MVG9uudbyLbNPZMtuxO54qpe.DK5jaS6q_pb7mBcusBAzQcItE_a2ZZoOSucuDuYqLgWgFd6iHKr6GUAWjWx"
            }
        },
        "Body": {
            "_ns": "soapenv",
            "query": {
                "_ns": "urn",
                "queryString": {
                    "_ns": "urn",
                    "text": "SELECT Id, Name FROM Account LIMIT 2"
                } 
            }
        }
    }
}
```

Which would return the following XML structure:

```xml
